{
  "doc_id": "36561",
  "text": "At present GIPC is the only known molecule interacting with the SEA motif of NRP-1. [CITATION_1] The in vivo relevance of this interaction was confirmed by knocking down GIPC in zebrafish giving rise to similar vascular defects as observed for NRP-1 knockdowns. [CITATION_2] It was also shown previously that GIPC, in combination with APPL1, interacts with another RTK, TrkA. [CITATION_3] Members of the APPL family are thus important adaptors located in the endosomal compartment that regulate signal specificity. [CITATION_4] Future experiments will show whether an APPL family member is involved in the formation of the VEGFR-2/NRP-1/GIPC complex.",
